	"system": {
		"description": "<p>The firework bursts into a wide cone of crackling sparks and force. Instead of its usual cylindrical area, the firework creates a 30-foot cone. Each creature in the cone must make a Strength saving throw or be pushed 15 feet away and fall prone. The area remains lightly obscured by smoke until the end of your next turn.</p><p>You can use an action to arm and launch a firework. You can do so a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus per short rest. Fireworks have a range of 120 feet, which increases by 30 feet at 5th, 11th, and 17th level. The area of effect is a cylinder with a 10-foot radius and a height of 30 feet, centered on the point of explosion. The radius increases by 10 feet and the height by 30 feet at 5th, 11th, and 17th level. You can choose the radius and height of the cylinder when you launch the firework.</p><p>The DC for all saving throws caused by your fireworks equals your spell save DC.</p>",
